# Pricing export definitions

cost_at_effective_price_default:
  * When applied to the Default consumption model its jut the cost of the usage at negotiated rates for that billing account before discounts are applied
  * When applied to a non default consumption model id it corresponds directly to a flex/spend cud and it represents what that spend cud covered. Ie its a credit.
  * for example if cost_at_effective_price_default = 10, cost = 6.50. The realized discount is $3.50
spend commit coverage:
  * Coverage is the whole on demand value of the usage
  * So for Default rows this just uses the cost
  * For spend commit rows you would use the cost_at_effective_price_default 





# General Definitions
on demand equivalent (ode): the price before any discounts are applied
on demand: remaining usage after all discounts are applied that is not recieving any discount and is paid at ode rates.



